
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ipsecme-ddos-protection-10.txt'>
    <title>"Protecting Internet Key Exchange Protocol version 2 (IKEv2) Implementations from Distributed Denial of Service Attacks", Yoav Nir, Valery Smyslov</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ipsecme-ddos-protection-10.txt</link>
    <description>This document recommends implementation and configuration best practices for Internet Key Exchange Protocol version 2 (IKEv2) Responders, to allow them to resist Denial of Service and Distributed Denial of Service attacks.  Additionally, the document introduces a new mechanism called "Client Puzzles" that help accomplish this task.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-10-01T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
